GreeHopper keeps reporting the error "Scrum boards are currently unavailable. An administrator must perform a re-index before you can use Scrum board functionality." even after performing the re-indexing. On analysis it is seen that the internal database variable that GreenHopper stores which indicates that a re-index is needed is not reset back even after re-indexing.

{panel:title=Workaround}
We have this knowledge article which explains the workaround for getting this error corrected. Please read - [Scrum Boards Fail to Open With Re-Indexing Error|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GHKB/Scrum+Boards+Fail+to+Open+With+Re-Indexing+Error]
{panel}

